<topic xml:id="glue-managing-users"
 role="glue" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>User administration using &cockpit;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        The &cockpit; <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> screen enables you to
        administer user accounts and groups.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <note>
    <title>User administration only for server administrators</title>
    <para>
      Only users with <guimenu>Administrative access</guimenu> can edit
      other users.
    </para>
  </note>
  <para>You can search and view the users, manage the user access and delete users.</para>
  <para>
    Using the <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> &cockpit; screen, you can perform the
    following tasks:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Creating new users of the system as described in
        <xref linkend="task-creating-users-cockpit"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem os="slemicro;slmicro" condition="5.5;6.0">
      <para>
        Creating new user groups as described in <xref linkend="cockpit-creating-groups"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Assigning <command>sudo</command> privileges to user accounts as described in
        <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Forcing a change of a user's password as described in
        <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Locking a particular user account as described in
        <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</topic>
